<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
</head>

<body class="bg-gray-50">
    <div class="min-h-screen py-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: November 2025 | Applicable Law: State of Utah</p>

                <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 mb-8">
                    <p class="text-blue-900 font-medium">
                        We are committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, share,
                        and protect your personal information.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="prose max-w-none space-y-6">
                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            When you register for an account or participate in our events, we collect the following
                            information:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email address, name (optional), and
                                account type (judge, participant, admin)</li>
                            <li><strong>Team Registration Information:</strong> Team name, project name, project
                                description, table location, and division</li>
                            <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Email address, project
                                links, GitHub/portfolio links</li>
                            <li><strong>Guardian Information:</strong> For users under 18 years of age, guardian email
                                address</li>
                            <li><strong>Communication Preferences:</strong> Email preferences for future events,
                                newsletters, and code-related content</li>
                            <li><strong>Project Details:</strong> Project descriptions, documentation, code
                                repositories, presentation materials</li>
                            <li><strong>Scores and Feedback:</strong> Scores entered by judges, judge notes and comments
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">1.2 Information Collected
                            Automatically</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            When you use our platform, we automatically collect certain information, including:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, device type,
                                operating system</li>
                            <li><strong>Usage Information:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, links clicked,
                                date and time of access</li>
                            <li><strong>Session Information:</strong> Login times, logout times, session duration</li>
                            <li><strong>Cookies and Similar Technologies:</strong> Session cookies for authentication
                                and JWT tokens stored in HTTP-only cookies</li>
                            <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> Server logs, error logs, security logs</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">1.3 Information from Third Parties
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We may receive information about you from:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Event Sponsors and Partners:</strong> If you interact with sponsors at our
                                events</li>
                            <li><strong>Social Media:</strong> If you choose to connect your social media accounts (if
                                applicable)</li>
                            <li><strong>Publicly Available Sources:</strong> Information from public GitHub profiles or
                                portfolios you link</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">2.1 Event Operations</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Process team registrations and manage event logistics</li>
                            <li>Assign judges to teams through our queue system</li>
                            <li>Calculate and display scores and leaderboards</li>
                            <li>Manage table assignments and venue logistics</li>
                            <li>Facilitate judging and scoring processes</li>
                            <li>Award prizes and recognition to winners</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">2.2 Communications</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Send event-related communications, updates, and announcements</li>
                            <li>Send magic link login emails for authentication</li>
                            <li>Contact guardians of users under 18 when required or appropriate</li>
                            <li>Send registration confirmations and account creation notifications</li>
                            <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
                            <li>Send important security or policy updates</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">2.3 Marketing (With Your Consent)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Send information about future code-camp events (if you opt-in)</li>
                            <li>Send newsletters and code-related educational content (if you opt-in)</li>
                            <li>Share success stories and event highlights (with your permission)</li>
                            <li>Promote future opportunities and programs</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">2.4 Platform Improvement</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Develop new features and enhance existing functionality</li>
                            <li>Troubleshoot technical issues and improve platform performance</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 text-sm italic">
                            Note: We do not currently analyze usage patterns or conduct internal research and analytics.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">2.5 Security and Legal Compliance</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Protect against fraud, abuse, and security threats</li>
                            <li>Enforce our Terms of Use and Acceptable Use Policy</li>
                            <li>Comply with legal obligations and respond to legal requests</li>
                            <li>Protect the rights, property, and safety of users and others</li>
                            <li>Investigate and prevent violations of our policies</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>

                        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4 mb-4">
                            <p class="text-green-900 font-bold">
                                We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties for their
                                marketing purposes.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We share your personal information only in the following limited circumstances:
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">3.1 Service Providers</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We may share information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in
                            operating our platform, including:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Email Service Providers:</strong> Mailgun (for sending transactional emails,
                                including magic link authentication and registration confirmations)</li>
                            <li><strong>Cloud Hosting:</strong> Hosting providers for our servers and databases</li>
                            <li><strong>Security Services:</strong> Services that help protect against fraud and abuse
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            These service providers are contractually obligated to protect your information, use it only
                            for the purposes we specify, and comply with applicable privacy laws.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">3.2 Event Partners and Sponsors</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            With your explicit consent, we may share limited information (such as name and email) with
                            event sponsors or partners who wish to provide you with relevant opportunities, resources,
                            or information.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">3.3 Legal Requirements</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We may disclose your information when required by law or in response to:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Subpoenas, court orders, or other legal processes</li>
                            <li>Requests from law enforcement or government agencies</li>
                            <li>Investigations of suspected illegal activity</li>
                            <li>Protection of our legal rights or property</li>
                            <li>Emergency situations involving danger to persons or property</li>
                        </ul>

                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Data Security</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We implement comprehensive security measures to protect your personal information,
                            including:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> All data transmitted between your device and our servers is
                                encrypted using SSL/TLS (enforced at the infrastructure level)</li>
                            <li><strong>Passwordless Authentication:</strong> We use magic link authentication via
                                email.
                                No passwords are stored. Authentication tokens (JWT) are stored in secure HTTP-only
                                cookies</li>
                            <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Limited employee and contractor access to personal
                                data on a need-to-know basis</li>
                            <li><strong>Regular Security Audits:</strong> Periodic review of security practices and
                                systems</li>
                            <li><strong>Secure Hosting:</strong> Data stored on secure servers with firewall protection
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>Token Security:</strong> JWT tokens expire after use and have limited lifetimes
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> Continuous monitoring for suspicious activity and security
                                threats</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            While we strive to protect your information using industry-standard practices, no method of
                            transmission or storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security, but we are
                            committed to protecting your data to the best of our ability.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            <strong>Security Breaches:</strong> In the event of a data breach affecting your personal
                            information, we will notify you and relevant authorities as required by applicable law,
                            typically within 72 hours of discovering the breach.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Children's Privacy (COPPA Compliance)
                        </h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We take the privacy of minors very seriously and comply with the Children's Online Privacy
                            Protection Act (COPPA) and Utah's privacy laws regarding minors.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">5.1 Users Under 18</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Users under 18 years of age are required to provide a guardian's email address during
                            registration. We will:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Notify guardians about their child's participation in the event</li>
                            <li>Require guardian consent for certain activities or data uses</li>
                            <li>Allow guardians to review, update, or delete their child's information</li>
                            <li>Provide guardians with access to privacy policy information</li>
                            <li>Limit the collection of personal information from minors to what is necessary for event
                                participation</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">5.2 Users Under 13</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            For users under 13 years of age, we require a guardian's email address during registration.
                            Guardians will receive a notification email about their child's participation. If you are a
                            guardian of a child under 13 and have concerns about their participation, please contact us
                            immediately using the contact information provided in Section 13.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">5.3 Guardian Rights</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Guardians of users under 18 have the right to:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Review what personal information has been collected from their child</li>
                            <li>Request deletion of their child's personal information</li>
                            <li>Refuse to allow further collection or use of their child's information</li>
                            <li>Update or correct their child's information</li>
                            <li>Receive notifications about data practices affecting their child</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            To exercise these rights, guardians can contact us using the information provided in Section
                            11.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We retain your personal information for different periods depending on the purpose:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Retained while your account is active and for a
                                reasonable period thereafter</li>
                            <li><strong>Event Data:</strong> Team registrations, scores, and event-related data may be
                                retained indefinitely for historical records and future event planning</li>
                            <li><strong>Communication Records:</strong> Email communications retained for up to 2 years
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> Server logs retained for up to 90 days</li>
                            <li><strong>Marketing Data:</strong> Retained until you opt-out or request deletion</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            <strong>Note:</strong> Automatic deletion based on retention periods is not currently
                            implemented. Data is retained until manually deleted or upon user request. You may request
                            deletion of your data at any time by contacting us using the information in Section 13. Some
                            information may be retained longer if required by law or to protect our legal rights.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You have the following rights regarding your personal information:
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">7.1 Access and Portability</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You have the right to request a copy of the personal information we hold about you. You can
                            export your data through your <a href="/account/settings"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline">account settings</a>,
                            which will provide a ZIP file containing all your data in JSON format along with all
                            associated images
                            (banner, logo, screenshots). Alternatively, you can contact us to request your data. We will
                            provide
                            this information within 30 days of your request.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">7.2 Correction and Update</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You can update your account information at any time through your account settings or by
                            contacting us. We will correct any inaccurate information promptly.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">7.3 Deletion</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You have the right to request deletion of your account and personal information. You can
                            delete your account through your <a href="/account/settings"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline">account settings</a>,
                            submit a <a href="/policies/data-removal-request"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline">data removal request form</a>,
                            or contact us to request deletion. We will delete your information within 30 days of your
                            request, except where:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>We are required by law to retain it</li>
                            <li>We need it to complete transactions you initiated</li>
                            <li>It is necessary to protect our legal rights</li>
                            <li>It has been aggregated or anonymized</li>
                            <li>Event data (scores, team registrations) may be retained for historical records</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">7.4 Opt-Out of Marketing</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Currently, we only send transactional emails (login links, registration confirmations,
                            etc.).
                            If we begin sending marketing communications in the future, you will be able to opt-out by:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Clicking the "unsubscribe" link in any marketing email</li>
                            <li>Updating your email preferences in your account settings</li>
                            <li>Contacting us directly to request removal</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Note: You cannot opt-out of essential service emails (login links, registration
                            confirmations, etc.).
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">7.5 Withdraw Consent</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Where we process your data based on consent, you have the right to withdraw that consent at
                            any time.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">7.6 Object to Processing</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You have the right to object to certain types of processing of your personal information.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">7.7 Lodge a Complaint</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            If you believe we have violated your privacy rights, you have the right to lodge a complaint
                            with a supervisory authority.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We use cookies and similar technologies to:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> Keep you logged in during your session</li>
                            <li><strong>JWT Tokens:</strong> Stored in HTTP-only cookies for secure authentication</li>
                            <li><strong>Security Cookies:</strong> Protect against fraud and enhance security</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            <strong>Note:</strong> We do not currently use preference cookies. User preferences are
                            stored in our database, not in cookies.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You can control cookies through your browser settings. Note that disabling cookies may limit
                            functionality of the platform.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">9. Third-Party Links</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Our platform may contain links to third-party websites (such as team project links, GitHub
                            repositories, etc.). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party
                            sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal
                            information.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">10. International Data Transfers</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Our servers are located in the United States. If you access our platform from outside the
                            United States, your information will be transferred to and processed in the United States,
                            which may have different data protection laws than your country.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices,
                            technology, legal requirements, or other factors. When we make changes:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>We will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
                            <li>For material changes, we will notify you via email or prominent notice on the platform
                            </li>
                            <li>We will obtain renewed consent if required by law</li>
                            <li>We encourage you to review this policy periodically</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Continued use of the platform after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated
                            policy.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">12. California Privacy Rights</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            If you are a California resident, you may have additional rights under the California
                            Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). While we are based in Utah, we respect the privacy rights of
                            all users. California residents may request information about how we share personal
                            information with third parties for their direct marketing purposes.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">13. Contact Us</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data
                            practices, please contact us:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Submit a <a href="/policies/data-removal-request"
                                    class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline">data removal request form</a>
                                for data deletion requests</li>
                            <li>Through your <a href="/account/settings"
                                    class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline">account settings</a> if you have
                                an account</li>
                            <li>By email at the address provided during event registration</li>
                            <li>By speaking with event administrators at the event venue</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We will respond to your inquiry within 30 days. For guardian requests regarding users under
                            18, we may require verification of your identity and relationship to the minor.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">14. Your Consent</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            By using our platform and participating in our events, you consent to the collection, use,
                            and sharing of your information as described in this Privacy Policy. For users under 18,
                            guardian consent is required and will be obtained separately.
                        </p>
                    </section>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
                    <a href="/register" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium">‚Üê Back to Registration</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
